The statement '(void) cls;' in ahc_echo is an executed no-op used solely to silence an unused-parameter compiler warning. Because cls is an ordinary (non-volatile) parameter and evaluating it has no side effects, removing this statement would not change program behaviour; thus it is dead code and violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.2.
